00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:13,920
 I've dreamed of becoming a really kick-butt CEO.

349
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:16,800
 I don't know if I'm allowed to say the word "butt" but I will just say it.

350
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:21,280
 And I've had a passion for the corporate world and the business world.

351
00:29:21,280 --> 00:29:25,600
 And for much of the last decade and a half I've been working since university,

352
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:28,960
 I felt I was very successful and confident in my career.

353
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:32,000
 You know, in these companies that I worked for,

354
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,800
 every year they would give annual performance reviews

355
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:37,200
 and I tended to place pretty high.

356
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:41,200
 So it just affirmed the confidence I had in myself that, you know,

357
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:42,880
 I'm a good leader, I'm a good worker,

358
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:46,160
 I'm recognized for my, you know, characteristics at work

359
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:50,320
 and identified as a high achiever.

360
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:53,520
 So when this incident came two years ago in the workplace,

361
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:55,200
 it was extremely hard for me.

362
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:58,640
 I had the toughest challenge yet in my career

363
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:01,040
 and I had a horrible relationship with my boss.

364
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:05,360
 And my relationship with him wasn't always strange,

365
00:30:05,360 --> 00:30:08,320
 but suddenly a year into working with him,

366
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:10,240
 things took a really bad turn.

367
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:14,000
 We would often have very big team meetings.

368
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:16,560
 Who has big team meetings, you know, when you have work?

369
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:19,360
 He, every time when I spoke up,

370
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:22,640
 I felt that he would vocally just humiliate me

371
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:24,160
 and turn the things down I said

372
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:25,840
 and make it known that, you know,

373
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:28,880
 what I was saying or suggesting was not the right way.

374
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:33,760
 And he would get very vocally nasty in front of the whole team

375
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:34,640
 and say that to me.

376
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:38,640
 And in other smaller team discussions, it was the same.

377
00:30:38,640 --> 00:30:42,160
 And, you know, he was very condescending in his speech.

378
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:46,880
 So I felt humiliated, I felt hurt, and I was surprised.

379
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:49,680
 And I tried to address this in our one-on-one discussions

380
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:50,800
 and ask him, you know,

381
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:53,280
 "How do you see me doing better, Mr. Boss?"

382
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,760
 Because obviously there's some issues.

383
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:57,520
 And it was a very hard discussion.

