00:30:57,520 --> 00:31:00,320
 He eventually never really gave any clear answers,

385
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:03,280
 but made it known that he would be hiring someone else

386
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:05,040
 to take over from my role.

387
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:06,640
 So that was very difficult for me.

388
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:07,840
 - Not easy, thank you.

389
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:12,560
 And Charles, could you share with us your family background?

390
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:14,240
 - Sure, good morning, everyone.

391
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:19,680
 I'm sharing a story from my family background.

392
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:23,440
 So I grew up in a family with a lot of relationship challenges.

393
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:26,000
 So there's a lot of emotional abuse

394
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,520
 happening within the family.

395
00:31:27,520 --> 00:31:30,400
 And eventually my parents are divorced.

396
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:34,720
 And my brother and I, after we got into university,

397
00:31:34,720 --> 00:31:38,800
 we moved out of the family just to be on our own

398
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:40,240
 so that we can have some peace.

399
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:44,400
 So at first I thought I just, I'm in a clear,

400
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:50,880
 but because the family didn't really have a common practice

401
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:52,720
 of forgiveness and apology.

402
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:55,760
 So I actually needed to learn it much later on

403
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:57,840
 in my adult life.

404
00:31:57,840 --> 00:32:03,120
 So I will share one example with you, one story with you.

405
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:07,120
 So this was when I was in my late 30s already.

406
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:12,400
 And at that time, my father was in his 80s

407
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:15,680
 and we were all living separately on our own.

408
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:17,600
 And one year he had a stroke.

409
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:21,120
 And then of course the family rallied together

410
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:23,120
 to try to care for my dad.

411
00:32:23,120 --> 00:32:26,400
 And during this time, we found out that he actually

412
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:29,120
 has been involved in a mess for a while

413
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:32,160
 and nobody in our family knew about it.

414
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:35,200
 So in order to help him out, I decided that

415
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:36,400
 at that time I was still single.

416
00:32:36,400 --> 00:32:40,720
 So I moved back to be with him.

417
00:32:40,720 --> 00:32:43,440
 I packed up half of my belongings.

418
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:44,000
 I moved back.

419
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:47,600
 I still kept my place, trying to support my dad

420
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:50,800
 and try to hopefully, hoping that he will not,

421
00:32:50,800 --> 00:32:53,920
 he will have a new life and not be involved

422
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:55,920
 in messy situations again.

423
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:58,720
 So long story short, after about six months,

424
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:03,360
 I realized that, my brother and I realized that

425
00:33:03,360 --> 00:33:04,960
 my dad is still involved in the mess.

426
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:08,080
 And I was very upset because I put in a lot of effort.

427
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:10,560
 My life was really difficult, going to work,

428
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:13,120
 having two places, having pets to look after,

429
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:15,120
 like just really chaos.

430
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:16,080
 So I was really obsessed.

431
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:17,840
 I packed my stuff and I went back home

432
00:33:17,840 --> 00:33:21,040
 and I just disassociated.

433
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:23,520
 So it felt like, okay, I'm back in my own place.

434
00:33:23,520 --> 00:33:25,760
 I should be feeling better now.

435
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:29,920
 And I learned a very valuable lesson during this season

436
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:33,120
 because when I moved back home for the next six months,

437
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:37,360
 I was tortured by memories.

438
00:33:37,360 --> 00:33:41,600
 And these are memories of my past wrongdoings,

439
00:33:41,600 --> 00:33:45,280
 things that I've done that I hurt people in the past.

440
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:47,680
 And these are old stuff as well

441
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,360
 that I thought I have resolved with God.

442
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:51,760
 I've confessed and I thought I received forgiveness.

443
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:54,800
 But these memories, for some reason,

444
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:58,480
 in that season came back and they would replay in my mind

445
00:33:58,480 --> 00:33:59,760
 like movie trailers.

446
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:05,040
 Imagine you have a movie trailer of your bad deeds playing.

447
00:34:05,040 --> 00:34:06,800
 That's really a torture actually.

448
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:10,160
 So after about six months, I really couldn't stand it.

449
00:34:10,160 --> 00:34:12,000
 So I was thinking to myself,

450
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:14,720
 what had actually really changed that this is happening?

451
00:34:14,720 --> 00:34:17,760
 And it still took me about two weeks to realize

452
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:20,720
 that it might be because I have held a grudge against my dad.

453
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:25,840
 And at that point, I realized that I really need to forgive my dad.

454
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,840
 And also at that point,

455
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:30,720
 because it was just a decision to forgive my dad,

456
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:33,200
 I also realized I was holding a grudge

457
00:34:33,200 --> 00:34:34,720
 based on my own choice as well.

458
00:34:34,720 --> 00:34:38,240
 And the forgiveness was also a choice that I could make.

459
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:40,480
 So I made the choice to forgive my dad.

460
00:34:40,480 --> 00:34:45,120
 When I made up with him, I totally behaved like normal again.

461
00:34:45,120 --> 00:34:49,440
 And actually, very, very, almost instantaneously,

462
00:34:50,240 --> 00:34:55,520
 all the tormenting videos would stop playing in my mind again.

463
00:34:55,520 --> 00:34:58,720
 So it was a very dramatic lesson for me.

464
00:34:58,720 --> 00:35:04,320
 And Charles, how did that impact you when you were growing up?

465
00:35:04,320 --> 00:35:07,040
 How did you cope with people?

